The snow hydrology port is already complete:

- **`src/biogeophys/snow_hydrology.jl`** — 2197 lines, 37 functions ported from the ~4070-line Fortran source
- **`test/test_snow_hydrology.jl`** — 522 lines, 22+ test categories
- **All 7889 tests pass**
- **Already committed** as `e878cf2 Port Snow hydrology from Fortran to Julia`

The only uncommitted changes are to `.ralph_last_output.log`, `.ralph_state`, and `PORTING_LOG.md` — these are automation/tracking files, not part of the port itself.

The port covers all 43 Fortran subroutines/functions including:
- New snow density calculation (Anderson 1976, Slater 2017, wind-dependent)
- Snow water balance and percolation
- Snow compaction (destructive, overburden, melt, wind drift metamorphism)
- Layer combination and division
- Snow capping
- Aerosol transport through snowpack
- Cold-start layer initialization
- Snow/no-snow filter construction

No further work is needed — the snow hydrology module is fully ported and passing all tests.
